# Security & Performance Guidelines

## Security Best Practices

- Sanitize user inputs to prevent XSS attacks
- Use react-native-encrypted-storage for sensitive data
- Ensure secure communication with APIs using HTTPS
- Follow Expo's Security guidelines: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/security/
- Validate all user inputs using Zod or similar libraries
- Implement proper authentication and authorization

## Performance Optimization

- Minimize useState and useEffect usage; prefer context and reducers
- Use Expo's AppLoading and SplashScreen for optimized startup
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data, implement lazy loading
- Implement code splitting and lazy loading with React.Suspense
- Use useMemo and useCallback hooks appropriately
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders by memoizing components

## Mobile Web Vitals

- Prioritize Load Time, Jank, and Responsiveness
- Use Expo's useWindowDimensions for responsive design
- Implement proper image optimization with expo-image
- Use react-native-reanimated for performant animations
- Profile and monitor performance using React Native's built-in tools

## State Management Performance

- Use React Context and useReducer for global state
- Leverage react-query for data fetching and caching
- Avoid excessive API calls
- Consider Zustand or Redux Toolkit for complex state
- Handle URL search parameters efficiently

## Memory Management

- Clean up subscriptions and timers in useEffect cleanup
- Avoid memory leaks in long-running components
- Use proper dependency arrays in useEffect
- Dispose of resources when components unmount
- Monitor memory usage in development

## Network Optimization

- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use request deduplication
- Handle offline scenarios gracefully
- Implement retry logic for failed requests
- Use appropriate timeout values

## Error Handling & Logging

- Use Zod for runtime validation
- Implement proper error logging with Sentry
- Use expo-error-reporter for production logging
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
- Implement global error boundaries

## Accessibility Performance

- Ensure high accessibility standards with ARIA roles
- Support text scaling and font adjustments
- Test with screen readers
- Implement proper focus management
- Use semantic HTML elements where possible

## Internationalization Performance

- Use react-native-i18n or expo-localization
- Support multiple languages efficiently
- Implement RTL layout support
- Cache translations appropriately
- Use lazy loading for translation files
